values: Well, Senior year is half over and I can't help feeling a little nostalgic already. I have done nothing very senior like and I am running out of chances. What is there to do besides skip classes? Been there, done that. I want to be remembered. This sucks.

WEEEEhooo! Christmas was yesterdayish and I got neato stuff........ A Nintendo DS and A remote car starter and a bunch of other awesome stuff. From Billy I got a BC Rich Warlock Bass and a black Coffin Case with red interior. He is also getting me an Amp. Woot woot. I hope everyone had a wonderful christmas to be remembered. 
Oh, by the way, Word to Jess!
Tag my Kesh Meister.
Blessed Be
Beky

The past few days have been extremely jam-packed full of stuff, most of it good. Last night I went to a Fall Out Boy, Motion City Soundtrack, Boys Night Out, Starting Line, and Panic at the Disco concert. It was VERY fun. Billy got me the tickets for my 17th birthday. It was our 4th or 5th time seeing Fall Out Boy. I got my shirt and my tattoo signed by Motion City Soundtrack. Justin actually touched my stomach.....woo woo.

Tonight Kesh and I are gonna party like its nineteen ninety nine. This should prove extremely amusing. Hopefully I dont zonk out in the middle because sleepwise I'm running on E.

Blessed Be,

Beky

I wonder if a livejournal would be the best way to go for my phsics journal.....that way it would be a live journal....haha, a pun....woot woot.......Tonight is supposed to be the "all-nighter" for my physics group. Well, I think that I might create a livejournal for physics then, off I go.....weeeeeeee...

Blessed Be,

Beky

Were starting out, we're starting over, MCC is the place to start.......
Well, I'm at id right now on my 10 minute break from Pre-calc.....I actually think I have to go......Tomorrow is Senior Picture Day!!!!! Woo Woo....not
Thanks for the bobbi pins, Kesh, they're cute....you'll get them back soon.
Blessed Be

Wow, I'm sooooo glad you can start posting again, Jess! We havent talked in like, ever. When are you going to pack up and move in with me?????? Reno is too far away. Counting down the days to christmas? I am.......76...I think. 
Well, I hope you can keep postin' regularly. Last night was homecoming dance. Senior year....holy shit......I got really sad afterward. On top of that, I had to work at 8:00 a.m. the next day. I ended up leaving Billy's at like 1:45 a.m I know for prom I am definitely not going to work the next morning. Today sucked horribly. After work I had to do my Physics homework....Mr. Boren is a stupid fuckhead.......grrrrrrrr......anyway, I will try to call you soon.....right now I have 7 classes including my college one. I am uber busy. Lots of love! Oh, by the way, I do remember playing Mother May I behind the restaurant. Do you remember staying up late in the living room playing Donkey Kong on the N-64??? That game reminds me of you. Lots of love, again!!
Blessed Be,
Beky

You Are 50% Boyish and 50% Girlish
You are pretty evenly split down the middle - a total eunuch. Okay, kidding about the eunuch part. But you do get along with both sexes. You reject traditional gender roles. However, you don't actively fight them. You're just you. You don't try to be what people expect you to be.
How Boyish or Girlish Are You?
I dont know how to take this....

Tonight was all about categorizing my 14 different types of leaves for my Plant Science leaf project. Lovely..... I am soooo sick of leaves. I never want to see another one again. For some reason I don't think this is possible. I finished the night off with doing my Physics homework. How high can I throw a ball???? FUCK YOU MR. BOREN!!!! d=Vi(T) + 1/2a(T^2).....I guess I can throw a ball 22 feet high......Taking in gravity into account. 
I ate a wonderful Veggie Delight sub from Subway for dinner. For lunch I had a can of spaghettio's(not heated) and for breakfast and brunch I had a special k bar and nachos and cheese, respectively. 
I ate no meat today! Woooohaa! Go me.
Well, I think Billy wants to do something other than watch me work all day so I better go give him a break from watching me do all of the work. HaHa......
Blessed Be

Today is a home football game and will be my first tailgating party.!!! I am super stoked because this is my senior year and tailgating parties are normally exclusive. Anyway, I am sending out my application to Wayne State, MSU, U of M, and Lawrence Tec very soon and am getting very excited/nervous about that. Hopefully I get accepted into all of them so I can choose where I go. Well, I'd better be going.
Blessed Be,
Beky

I have written in a while because wee just recvently got the internet back. I supose that Jess isnt goit to keep updating her journal because she should be back home by now......I think......I never did get to go back down to Texas. Oh well. I just celebrated my 17th birthday.... 8-8-88...horah! I feel no different whatsoever, but I guess that always happens on one's birthday. The only difference is I can drive late if I want to. Well, I better get back to downloading Blackbird from the Beatles. I'm going to try to play that stupid song by the end of the day....oh crap, I work tonight.....well, I guess I'm going to try to play most of it by the end of the day.

Billy and I are going to Texas/Arkansas probably around the same time my sister goes. We will probably be staying at my grandpa's house because I dont know if my uncle will allow Billy to stay at his house. 
Jess, I miss you! Things sound exciting at your house with the new kittens and puppy! I am coming to visit probably the end of July. 
I hope Colin is recovering. Keep posting and maybe someday I will reply to a post!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
Stop being so God Damned bored, Get your ass out of the house and into that skimpy little bathing suit and on that hot hot trampoline!
You better be at least as dark as me when I get there!!!!!!
Until then, Blessed Be!

Hey Jess!
If you're out there, I miss you!!!! I hope you are reading the book I left for you to read! Today was such a boring day! I wish I could be laying out in the sun with you on the trampoline! 
Today wasn't a total loss, I went to a pet store with Billy and got 3 fish for the fish tank! They are so cool! You can see through them except in their intestines, the company that stocks them injects a neon dye! So I have two see through fish with lime green and neon pink intestines! I have another kind of fish that is soooo shiny! He is a baby blue color, I think you would like him the best!
I made Billy watch Spanglish with me this morning! He liked it soooo much. 
Today it rained so hard that you couldnt see through your windshield. It sucked. I start tanning tomorrow to get rid of my tan lines.
My dress came in the mail yesterday and it fits me awesomely!
I hope my shoes come soon.
Well, I better get to bed. I have to work tomorrow.
Night

Yay!!!! Today is Sunday and I get to see my boyfriend on Wednesday!!!! I havent seen him since last Sunday because, as you probably know, He did not come with me to Texas. Oh well, ten days is almost over! I'm so excited. Last night we had to babysit our cousins and when My aunt got back today, she was livid! Her baby boy convinced her that my cousin had been a heathen and no one can convince her otherwise. So, like usual, her son is getting A+ Treatment and my cousin gets punished and yelled at for doing nothing wrong. Oh well, I guess you have to choose your battles, huh.

Merry Meet,
Whats one day late? 
Today is another long, hot day in Sunny Texas. So far, the high today is 104 with absolutely NO BREEZE!!!! 
I just love to fry like an egg in a steamy mini van. Fun fun fun. 
Currently, I am bored out of my mind and thinking of my hunky man slaving away in a kitchen some thousand miles away. I'm sure he's having sooo much more fun than me. ;P 
Well, I'm getting super excited about my birthday coming up in August. Can't wait for no driving restrictions. (Not that I ever get pulled over for driving past midnight anyway)
Senior year is a few short months away and I am so excited I can hardly stand it. It will be my last year of Wings of Harmony and I'll get all of the seniority. I'm sure by the last month of school I'll be begging for more time in my Youth. But, until then, pleeaasse get over with so I can get married and have kids and go to College and have my own house and not care about run on sentences. (haha)
Well, enoughs enough I guess.
Blessed Be

Merry Meet!
    
Currently, I am in Texas visiting my Uncle and his bratty children. This is day four of ten that I must spend "down South." I am so ready to go home it is unreal. I want to spend time with my friends and listen to my music and play my guitar. For some reason, I thought ten days would go by fast and I would be having a great time. Well, I am a complete idiot. I don't know what the HelL I was thinking but I'm sure I wont be thinking it ever again. 
I found my way to Live Journal after realizing I forgot my member name and password to Dead Journal. Its very sad but I am afraid my account there might have been terminated. Oh well, I must make the best of this one. 
It is 11:38 pm in Texas which means that back in Michigan it is 12:38 am. Fun fun fun, fun in the sun. NOT!
Not fun in the sun. Hell in the sun. Today when I woke up it was already 95 outside. That promised a horrible hot, sweaty day. I dont know why anyone in their right mnd would want to live in such a hot hot hot place.
The only good thing about this place is that I get to spend time with my cousin from Reno. She is visitng her Dad for the summer. I also enjoy spending time with my uncle, whom I rarely get to see. His wife is very funny in her own quirky way. Lets just say she needs to have a girl of her own before the boys drive her mad.
Well, I'm sure I keeping everyone up with my typing. 
Blessed Be!
